        "category": "classfeature",
        "description": {
            "value": "<p>You specialize in targeting foes from far away and attacking while unseen. Whether you're peeking around a corner, perching on a distant rooftop, or aiming from the back line of a squad formation, you favor sniper rifles and prefer to line up the perfect shot rather than rush into combat. You're trained in Stealth. You gain a skill feat for Stealth.</p>\n<p><strong>Exploit:</strong> You ignore the unwieldy and volley trait of guns you wield belonging to the sniper group. You gain one of the following operative feats as a bonus feat: @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.feats.Item.Keep Them in Your Sights] or @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.feats.Item.Scope Sight].</p>\n<p><strong>Enhanced Exploit:</strong> If you fail your first ranged Strike against your mark using a weapon in the sniper weapon group, you Reload your sniper weapon as a free action. The Strike doesn't count toward your multiple attack penalty.</p>"
        },
